    "narrative": "The lineup for LawDog today leans heavily into favorable matchups against vulnerable starters, with **Tyler Freeman** (72.83) headlining the slate. His elite score is driven by a massive +14% park factor and a soft matchup against Javier, coupled with the security of the #2 spot in the order. **Bryson Stott** (68.59) and **Lawrence Butler** (66.38) also project as high-floor pivots; both benefit from significant SP skill bonuses against Mahle and Warren, respectively. While **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** is an elite talent, his matchup against a premier arm in Ragans results in a middling 56.26, reminding us that even our best studs are susceptible to tough left-handed opposition.\n\nWe have maintained a disciplined stance on the bench today, specifically concerning **Luis Arraez**, who posted a 55.38. While his contact profile is reliable, he failed to crack the starting nine because his output didn't offer the same upside as **Geraldo Perdomo** (59.33) or the platoon-advantaged **Jonathan Aranda** (62.83). **Gleyber Torres** remains a start despite the SP skill bonus being partially negated by a platoon disadvantage against Ober, a decision reflecting our reliance on his order position and wind-aided potential. We are monitoring the weather closely, but the primary risk remains the high-end talent of opposing starters like Ohtani, who suppresses the ceiling for **Daulton Varsho** (50.93) despite the favorable platoon split. We are prioritizing total daily efficiency to maximize our cap usage across these favorable matchups.",
